1
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:48,720
(Thank You, Doctor)
[K💖I💖S💖S💖K💖H]

2
00:01:48,720 --> 00:01:51,600
(Adapted from Sheng Li's novel "ICU 48 Hours")

3
00:01:51,839 --> 00:01:54,640
(Episode 31)
[K💖I💖S💖S💖K💖H]

4
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:57,080
Xiao Rui.

5
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,839
Xiao Rui!

6
00:02:02,119 --> 00:02:03,800
Can I have a word with you?

7
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:08,479
If you want to blame someone, blame me.

8
00:02:10,160 --> 00:02:11,880
I apologize to you.

9
00:02:11,919 --> 00:02:13,000
Mom.

10
00:02:15,280 --> 00:02:16,280
I know.

11
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:17,800
You did that...

12
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,160
because of what happened to your mom.

13
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,839
But you can't leave your dad to die...

14
00:02:23,199 --> 00:02:25,000
just for this one thing.

15
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:26,199
Mom.

16
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,199
You didn't do anything wrong.

17
00:02:28,839 --> 00:02:30,079
You don't need to apologize.

18
00:02:32,440 --> 00:02:33,479
Su Rui.

19
00:02:33,519 --> 00:02:34,759
Are you crazy?

20
00:02:35,199 --> 00:02:37,519
Don't you know what the situation was back then?

21
00:02:37,880 --> 00:02:40,079
Your mom thought my dad couldn't make money,

22
00:02:40,079 --> 00:02:41,919
so she got on with her boss.

23
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,239
It became a mess and she wanted to divorce my dad.

24
00:02:44,359 --> 00:02:45,799
Then her boss didn't want her anymore,

25
00:02:46,039 --> 00:02:47,560
so she wanted to reconcile with my dad.

26
00:02:47,690 --> 00:02:49,039
Is that possible? You're a man too.

27
00:02:49,039 --> 00:02:50,280
Would you be able to accept it?

28
00:02:50,799 --> 00:02:53,160
My dad met my mom after he divorced your mom.

29
00:02:53,239 --> 00:02:55,239
My dad felt terrible that your mom got sick and passed away.

30
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:57,410
Do you know how long he was sad for?

31
00:02:57,410 --> 00:02:59,280
- Shut up! - Let me tell you, Su Rui.

32
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,639
This all started because of your mom.

33
00:03:00,639 --> 00:03:01,919
It's your mom's fault!

34
00:03:01,970 --> 00:03:03,359
- No... - What are you doing?

35
00:03:04,160 --> 00:03:05,160
This is a hospital.

36
00:03:12,519 --> 00:03:13,560
Xiao Rui.

37
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:17,440
It's bad blood of the previous generation.

38
00:03:17,880 --> 00:03:19,400
It's all in the past.

39
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:22,039
Now,

40
00:03:22,440 --> 00:03:23,759
you're the only one...

41
00:03:24,359 --> 00:03:25,400
who can save your dad.

42
00:03:35,039 --> 00:03:36,799
I'm begging you.

43
00:03:40,239 --> 00:03:41,560
Mom, please get up.

44
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:44,160
Please save him.

45
00:03:44,519 --> 00:03:46,079
- Mom, get up. - Xiao Rui.

46
00:03:46,319 --> 00:03:47,319
Save him!

47
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:48,440
Mom.

48
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:51,000
Xiao Rui!

49
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,720
Xiao Rui.

50
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,639
Do you want your dad to die?

51
00:03:58,759 --> 00:03:59,759
Xiao Rui.

52
00:04:00,359 --> 00:04:01,639
I'm begging you.

53
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,840
Please save your dad.

54
00:04:09,759 --> 00:04:11,680
I'm begging you...

55
00:04:18,919 --> 00:04:20,680
This is what he chose.

56
00:04:23,199 --> 00:04:24,560
Xiao Rui!

57
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,359
Xiao Rui, come back.

58
00:04:27,759 --> 00:04:29,680
Ma'am, please get up.

59
00:04:29,840 --> 00:04:30,960
We'll think of something else.

60
00:04:32,039 --> 00:04:33,079
Mom.

61
00:04:39,679 --> 00:04:40,999
It's 38.5 degrees Celsius.

62
00:04:47,879 --> 00:04:49,559
Dr. Bai, the test results are out.

63
00:04:52,039 --> 00:04:53,879
The CT scan result shows no obvious abnormalities.

64
00:04:56,359 --> 00:04:57,600
CKIs are elevated.

65
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:58,879
Protein is low.

66
00:04:59,239 --> 00:05:00,400
There's a problem with his heart.

67
00:05:00,479 --> 00:05:01,520
Ultrasound.

68
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:14,439
Decreased heart valve activity.

69
00:05:17,479 --> 00:05:18,559
His spleen is enlarged.

70
00:05:18,770 --> 00:05:20,879
He also has a high fever...

71
00:05:21,330 --> 00:05:22,770
which is causing hypoproteinemia.

72
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,999
Is it an autoimmune disease?

73
00:05:25,119 --> 00:05:26,239
It's possible.

74
00:05:26,239 --> 00:05:27,280
We'll do this.

75
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:29,330
Run another antibody test for the patient.

76
00:05:41,080 --> 00:05:43,119
How is Xiao Rui?

77
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:44,999
Dad.

78
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,479
He doesn't care whether you live or die.

79
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:49,280
Why do you still care about him?

80
00:05:49,799 --> 00:05:51,400
Don't talk to your dad like that.

81
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,359
He was fine.

82
00:05:55,479 --> 00:05:57,479
Why did he faint?

83
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,559
Did the doctor say...

84
00:05:59,799 --> 00:06:01,720
if it's serious?

85
00:06:02,119 --> 00:06:03,359
He deserved it.

86
00:06:04,479 --> 00:06:05,479
Get out.

87
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:07,400
Go.

88
00:06:10,799 --> 00:06:12,239
I just asked the doctor.

89
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:13,999
They don't know what it is yet...

90
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,479
and still need to run some tests.

91
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,679
I hope it's nothing serious.

92
00:06:21,879 --> 00:06:23,799
I don't know how things turned out like this.

93
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:26,559
Ming Jun.

94
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,999
You should worry about yourself.

95
00:06:29,999 --> 00:06:33,239
When his mom passed away,

96
00:06:34,200 --> 00:06:37,559
I should have taken him with me.

97
00:06:39,160 --> 00:06:41,919
He suffered so much...

98
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:45,080
while living with his uncles.

99
00:06:49,039 --> 00:06:51,999
I was too selfish.

100
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:53,799
It's not your fault.

101
00:06:54,919 --> 00:06:56,039
It's mine.

102
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:58,799
When I was pregnant with Xin Xin,

103
00:06:59,679 --> 00:07:01,280
I was afraid I couldn't take care of Xiao Rui...

104
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:02,679
if he came.

105
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:06,879
I didn't know it would be like this.

106
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:09,520
The person he should hate the most is me.

107
00:07:10,760 --> 00:07:11,799
It's me.

108
00:07:31,679 --> 00:07:33,640
The patient's son is so cruel.

109
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:34,879
I know.

110
00:07:35,119 --> 00:07:37,280
First, he agreed to the transplant and gave him hope.

111
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,600
At the last minute,

112
00:07:38,879 --> 00:07:39,999
he pulled out.

113
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:42,160
He said it's the punishment for what the patient did back then.

114
00:07:42,239 --> 00:07:43,520
That's too cruel.

115
00:07:43,960 --> 00:07:44,960
Else, how could he...

116
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:46,999
a president of such a big company at such a young age?

117
00:07:47,439 --> 00:07:48,799
Cruelty is a skill too.

118
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,200
Ya Jie.

119
00:07:52,239 --> 00:07:54,200
If your Bai Zhu is also that cruel,

120
00:07:55,119 --> 00:07:56,359
would you still want to marry him?

121
00:07:57,799 --> 00:07:59,679
Bai Zhu has the softest heart.

122
00:07:59,879 --> 00:08:01,799
He'll never be this cruel.

123
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,999
Seems like you won't be able to do anything big in this life.

124
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:11,679
For richer or for poorer,

125
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:14,080
I will be with him for the rest of my life.

126
00:08:16,119 --> 00:08:17,359
The wedding vows are out.

127
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,799
There's no point in being jealous. This is called being a fool.

128
00:08:22,840 --> 00:08:23,879
Hello.

129
00:08:25,280 --> 00:08:26,760
Okay, I got it.

130
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:29,960
The test results are out. Let's go.

131
00:08:30,119 --> 00:08:31,200
I'll go take a look too.

132
00:08:31,879 --> 00:08:33,720
You're all leaving?

133
00:08:37,840 --> 00:08:38,919
Boring.

134
00:08:44,879 --> 00:08:45,960
How is it?

135
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:47,960
The antibody test showed...

136
00:08:48,039 --> 00:08:49,320
that it's not an autoimmune disease.

137
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:50,999
Could it be an infection then?

138
00:08:57,399 --> 00:08:59,440
Run another blood test and a CT scan.

139
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,519
Okay.

140
00:09:03,479 --> 00:09:04,840
Based on the results,

141
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:06,050
I think it's an infection.

142
00:09:07,810 --> 00:09:09,840
There are so many kinds of pathogens that can cause infections.

143
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:10,999
Which one could it be?

144
00:09:11,159 --> 00:09:13,519
Based on the test results and symptoms so far,

145
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:14,639
I don't see any abnormalities.

146
00:09:14,639 --> 00:09:15,930
I can't tell which one it is.

147
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:18,720
Should we send for a sputum culture and blood culture test?

148
00:09:18,999 --> 00:09:20,720
But the cultures take time to cultivate.

149
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:22,440
I'm afraid it'll take about a week...

150
00:09:22,479 --> 00:09:23,690
for the results.

151
00:09:24,050 --> 00:09:25,279
The patient can't wait that long.

152
00:09:25,399 --> 00:09:26,720
Do you have a better idea?

153
00:09:29,810 --> 00:09:30,810
I'm sure there is.

154
00:09:34,119 --> 00:09:35,690
Let's do a sputum smear first.

155
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,320
Maybe we'll find something.

156
00:09:38,479 --> 00:09:39,600
Let's go to the lab.

157
00:09:44,359 --> 00:09:45,519
Okay, you can get the medicine.

158
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,879
Okay. Thank you, Dr. Bai.

159
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,479
We found a matching bone marrow.

160
00:09:50,320 --> 00:09:51,639
Heping Hospital just uploaded...

161
00:09:51,639 --> 00:09:53,690
a bone marrow donor's profile.

162
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:55,359
It's not a perfect match.

163
00:09:55,359 --> 00:09:56,690
For Human Leukocyte Antigen testing,

164
00:09:56,690 --> 00:09:58,359
four out of six can be a match.

165
00:09:58,519 --> 00:10:00,999
Half-match transplants can cause severe rejection.

166
00:10:00,999 --> 00:10:02,050
At least,

167
00:10:02,050 --> 00:10:03,519
it'll give him a chance to live.

168
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,810
He will live the rest of his life in pain.

169
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:07,200
Just like Jiang Xian Yun.

170
00:10:07,479 --> 00:10:09,560
No, there's a critical problem.

171
00:10:09,759 --> 00:10:12,320
He doesn't have time to wait for a perfect bone marrow match.

172
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,759
I've uploaded his information...

173
00:10:13,759 --> 00:10:14,810
to the foreign bone marrow bank.

174
00:10:14,879 --> 00:10:16,119
They'll get back to us soon.

175
00:10:16,200 --> 00:10:18,720
Let's put aside the low probability of a successful match.

176
00:10:19,399 --> 00:10:21,050
Even if, we find a suitable bone marrow donor,

177
00:10:21,119 --> 00:10:22,159
they are abroad.

178
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:23,810
Can they come for the transplant in time?

179
00:10:23,879 --> 00:10:25,960
We can't joke around with the patient's life.

180
00:10:25,960 --> 00:10:27,519
I'm not joking.

181
00:10:27,879 --> 00:10:29,479
I'll contact the donor later...

182
00:10:29,479 --> 00:10:30,810
and tell them to be prepared.

183
00:10:30,999 --> 00:10:32,239
But this is my last option.

184
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,440
I'll emphasize this once more.

185
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:35,440
The patient has only a few days left.

186
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:36,840
- Let's not... - Don't argue with me.

187
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,639
I'm his attending doctor. Listen to me.

188
00:10:42,639 --> 00:10:43,720
Okay, listen up.

189
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:45,930
He's no longer your patient.

190
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,720
I'll take on this patient myself.

191
00:10:51,119 --> 00:10:52,119
Sure.

192
00:10:52,810 --> 00:10:53,930
Take him on if you're so good.

193
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,359
Take them all.

194
00:10:59,399 --> 00:11:00,810
A half-match transplant...

195
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,600
could lead to serious rejection.

196
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,930
So we'll put this plan at the end.

197
00:11:05,159 --> 00:11:06,279
Until then,

198
00:11:06,279 --> 00:11:08,399
we'll keep looking for a suitable bone marrow.

199
00:11:08,479 --> 00:11:09,479
Doctor.

200
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:13,200
You just said that if he's unlucky...

201
00:11:13,690 --> 00:11:15,639
and no pathogen can be detected,

202
00:11:15,960 --> 00:11:18,479
Xiao Rui won't make it.

203
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:22,759
I was talking about your condition.

204
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,200
Tell me.

205
00:11:25,159 --> 00:11:27,359
Is Xiao Rui in danger?

206
00:11:30,879 --> 00:11:32,680
The culture results aren't out yet.

207
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:34,840
For the time being, we can only administer medication empirically.

208
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,800
Is there anything I can do?

209
00:11:38,399 --> 00:11:40,279
Sometimes, diagnosing takes time.

210
00:11:40,519 --> 00:11:41,680
We have to observe...

211
00:11:41,759 --> 00:11:42,840
the development of his condition...

212
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:44,840
and give him a few more tests...

213
00:11:44,999 --> 00:11:47,239
to see what caused the disease.

214
00:11:47,560 --> 00:11:50,519
Let's say someone has the same sickness.

215
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:52,680
They're sicker...

216
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:53,960
and have more symptoms.

217
00:11:54,200 --> 00:11:56,320
Could you be able to find out...

218
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,680
the cause of the disease faster?

219
00:11:59,479 --> 00:12:01,359
Well, it's possible.

220
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:03,920
Then I'm willing to be infected.

221
00:12:05,479 --> 00:12:06,519
What?

222
00:12:06,759 --> 00:12:09,080
This could be the chance...

223
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:11,920
God is giving me to atone for my sins.

224
00:12:12,119 --> 00:12:14,359
If you're infected with the pathogen in your condition,

225
00:12:14,399 --> 00:12:15,479
there will be no hope for you.

226
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,279
A life for a life.

227
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,080
If my death...

228
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,600
can save my son,

229
00:12:21,680 --> 00:12:22,720
I'll accept it.

230
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:24,359
Don't think too much.

231
00:12:24,399 --> 00:12:25,879
We won't let you do that.

232
00:12:27,119 --> 00:12:28,239
Don't be too pessimistic.

233
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,560
As for the bone marrow,

234
00:12:29,639 --> 00:12:30,759
we'll continue to find it for you.

235
00:12:30,999 --> 00:12:32,080
Have a good rest.

236
00:12:33,200 --> 00:12:34,359
My illness...

237
00:12:35,040 --> 00:12:36,639
is incurable.

238
00:12:38,040 --> 00:12:40,440
If I could find the right bone marrow,

239
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,279
I would have found it a long time ago.

240
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,239
I have leukemia.

241
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:48,080
It has come and gone for three times.

242
00:12:49,759 --> 00:12:52,080
I don't want to suffer anymore.

243
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:53,639
Doctor.

244
00:12:53,879 --> 00:12:56,879
Please let me die in peace.

245
00:12:57,320 --> 00:13:00,200
Let me do something for Xiao Rui.

246
