490
00:25:17,359 --> 00:25:18,919
How's Su Ming Jun?

491
00:25:19,639 --> 00:25:21,560
His problem is more serious now.

492
00:25:21,879 --> 00:25:23,199
He's now in a coma.

493
00:25:23,879 --> 00:25:26,000
We'll also prepare the donor for surgery...

494
00:25:26,159 --> 00:25:27,240
and operate as soon as possible.

495
00:25:28,760 --> 00:25:30,119
But it's not a perfect match.

496
00:25:30,439 --> 00:25:31,560
After the surgery,

497
00:25:31,679 --> 00:25:34,320
he'll suffer a lot and be in a lot of pain.

498
00:25:34,639 --> 00:25:36,520
But at least, he gets to live.

499
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:44,800
We know...

500
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:46,800
you don't want to get too involved...

501
00:25:46,919 --> 00:25:48,240
with your dad.

502
00:25:48,719 --> 00:25:50,040
But your dad couldn't do that.

503
00:25:50,679 --> 00:25:53,159
When he knew you had a serious illness...

504
00:25:53,159 --> 00:25:55,719
where your life might be in danger and we couldn't find the cause,

505
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:57,600
he told us...

506
00:25:57,639 --> 00:25:59,480
he wanted to get infected by the same pathogen...

507
00:25:59,679 --> 00:26:00,879
and have the same illness...

508
00:26:01,439 --> 00:26:03,840
to help us doctors find out the cause of the disease faster.

509
00:26:04,359 --> 00:26:05,439
But don't worry.

510
00:26:06,520 --> 00:26:08,320
We wouldn't let him do that.

511
00:26:09,080 --> 00:26:11,520
To a patient with advanced leukemia,

512
00:26:11,719 --> 00:26:13,119
it's equivalent to suicide.

513
00:26:13,639 --> 00:26:15,359
But your dad insisted.

514
00:26:15,719 --> 00:26:17,520
He found a bone marrow donor,

515
00:26:17,959 --> 00:26:19,080
although not a perfect match,

516
00:26:19,159 --> 00:26:20,639
he'll live at least.

517
00:26:21,280 --> 00:26:22,359
But he...

518
00:26:23,159 --> 00:26:25,359
is willing to give up his own life to save you.

519
00:26:26,159 --> 00:26:27,639
He said it's because you're his son.

520
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:29,480
He owes you too much.

521
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,320
As a dad, he has to do that.

522
00:26:36,439 --> 00:26:37,560
Actually,

523
00:26:37,959 --> 00:26:39,639
after these few days,

524
00:26:39,719 --> 00:26:40,800
we can tell...

525
00:26:41,199 --> 00:26:42,240
that you and your dad...

526
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,719
still care about each other.

527
00:26:45,600 --> 00:26:47,439
Mr. Su, have you ever thought...

528
00:26:47,679 --> 00:26:48,719
about why...

529
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:51,320
your love for your dad is out of place?

530
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:53,560
He's at that age...

531
00:26:53,639 --> 00:26:55,520
to wait for his children's gratitude.

532
00:26:55,919 --> 00:26:58,359
But you've been waiting for your dad's apology.

533
00:27:00,919 --> 00:27:02,320
There's an old saying that goes,

534
00:27:02,359 --> 00:27:03,879
"When the child wants to repay, the parents are no longer around."

535
00:27:05,399 --> 00:27:06,560
As doctors,

536
00:27:06,639 --> 00:27:08,679
we've seen too many life and death.

537
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:11,119
We've felt too many regrets that were never expressed.

538
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,399
You and your dad still have time.

539
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:15,959
You have a chance.

540
00:27:16,719 --> 00:27:18,280
Why don't you cherish it?

541
00:27:28,919 --> 00:27:29,959
Dr. Xiao.

542
00:27:32,199 --> 00:27:33,600
If I do the transplant now,

543
00:27:34,600 --> 00:27:35,800
will it be too late?

544
00:27:41,719 --> 00:27:42,879
He really agreed?

545
00:27:44,199 --> 00:27:45,919
Is he trying to trick us again?

546
00:27:45,919 --> 00:27:46,959
Don't worry.

547
00:27:46,959 --> 00:27:48,560
Once his condition stabilizes,

548
00:27:48,560 --> 00:27:49,800
I'll have the hematologist...

549
00:27:49,879 --> 00:27:50,879
start the evaluation right away.

550
00:27:52,679 --> 00:27:53,719
That's great!

551
00:27:56,320 --> 00:27:57,359
Ming Jun.

552
00:27:57,679 --> 00:27:58,879
You can be saved.

553
00:27:59,280 --> 00:28:00,639
You can be saved, Ming Jun.

554
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,040
Dr. Bai.

555
00:28:07,080 --> 00:28:08,080
You're not leaving, are you?

556
00:28:08,080 --> 00:28:09,080
Where to?

557
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:10,760
Didn't you say you're leaving the EICU?

558
00:28:11,959 --> 00:28:13,000
Who told you that?

559
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:14,560
So you're not leaving?

560
00:28:14,719 --> 00:28:15,760
Don't listen to nonsense.

561
00:28:15,919 --> 00:28:17,359
That day, I wanted to tell you...

562
00:28:17,359 --> 00:28:19,119
that I believe you.

563
00:28:22,480 --> 00:28:23,879
Too late. It doesn't count.

564
00:28:37,800 --> 00:28:39,199
I'm here to apologize.

565
00:28:39,959 --> 00:28:41,000
Earlier,

566
00:28:41,159 --> 00:28:42,280
I was too impulsive.

567
00:28:42,520 --> 00:28:43,639
I shouldn't have said that about you.

568
00:28:47,639 --> 00:28:49,320
Actually, you don't have to apologize to me.

569
00:28:50,480 --> 00:28:51,959
You were right.

570
00:28:53,240 --> 00:28:54,399
Sometimes,

571
00:28:54,800 --> 00:28:55,840
I indeed...

572
00:28:56,000 --> 00:28:57,879
want to show off my skills.

573
00:29:00,560 --> 00:29:01,719
But it can't be helped.

574
00:29:02,080 --> 00:29:03,119
Excellent people...

575
00:29:03,240 --> 00:29:04,560
have high expectations of themselves.

576
00:29:07,119 --> 00:29:08,119
But...

577
00:29:09,359 --> 00:29:10,600
I should apologize to you too.

578
00:29:11,760 --> 00:29:13,000
I was rude before.

579
00:29:14,199 --> 00:29:15,240
Okay.

580
00:29:15,679 --> 00:29:17,520
Let's put this behind us.

581
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:22,439
There are still many things to do.

582
00:29:22,679 --> 00:29:23,679
Get back to work.

583
00:29:57,240 --> 00:29:58,280
Xin Xin.

584
00:29:58,919 --> 00:30:00,040
Your dad is awake.

585
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:08,480
Dad.

586
00:30:28,719 --> 00:30:33,719
(Xiao Rui is fine.)

587
00:31:19,919 --> 00:31:21,119
Brother.

588
00:31:24,719 --> 00:31:25,800
Thank you.

589
00:31:33,359 --> 00:31:34,399
Let's go.

590
00:31:44,679 --> 00:31:46,520
Okay. Is everyone here?

591
00:31:46,679 --> 00:31:48,399
I have something to announce.

592
00:31:48,639 --> 00:31:50,919
This year's Hospital Development Conference...

593
00:31:50,919 --> 00:31:51,959
is being held.

594
00:31:52,480 --> 00:31:53,520
This conference...

595
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,280
has garnered great attention...

596
00:31:55,520 --> 00:31:56,639
from the national media.

597
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:59,600
It is the most grand industry event...

598
00:31:59,919 --> 00:32:00,959
of the year

599
00:32:01,359 --> 00:32:03,000
Is our department taking part? I'll sign up.

600
00:32:04,359 --> 00:32:05,800
We've had too many patients lately.

601
00:32:05,879 --> 00:32:07,760
We won't assign any staff to take part.

602
00:32:07,919 --> 00:32:09,040
According to hospital regulations,

603
00:32:09,439 --> 00:32:11,840
tomorrow, a committee of the Hospital Development Conference...

604
00:32:11,919 --> 00:32:14,080
will come to our department...

605
00:32:14,199 --> 00:32:15,439
for a survey visit.

606
00:32:15,639 --> 00:32:17,080
Everyone must take it seriously.

607
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:18,760
Is bowing down to them...

608
00:32:18,919 --> 00:32:20,199
and flattery enough?

609
00:32:21,439 --> 00:32:22,520
Don't joke around.

610
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:24,320
Well...

611
00:32:24,359 --> 00:32:25,679
Don't worry, everyone.

612
00:32:25,800 --> 00:32:27,399
Just see your patients...

613
00:32:27,399 --> 00:32:29,080
and work as usual.

614
00:32:29,199 --> 00:32:30,639
Yes, Yi Ran.

615
00:32:30,919 --> 00:32:32,760
You'll be in charge of welcoming the committee tomorrow.

616
00:32:32,919 --> 00:32:33,919
No.

617
00:32:34,119 --> 00:32:35,119
It's decided.

618
00:32:35,879 --> 00:32:37,280
That's it. Dismissed.

619
00:32:37,560 --> 00:32:39,000
- Get back to work. - No, Dr. Lu.

620
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:40,320
Come. Come with me...

621
00:32:40,320 --> 00:32:41,520
to see the patient in bed five.

622
00:32:43,040 --> 00:32:44,280
Have you looked for his family?

623
00:32:44,439 --> 00:32:45,480
Yes.

624
00:32:51,879 --> 00:32:54,080
Isn't welcoming the committee a good thing?

625
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:56,760
It's easy to get to know the elites in the industry.

626
00:32:57,199 --> 00:32:59,280
Why does Dr. Xu look so unhappy?

627
00:33:00,119 --> 00:33:01,240
So materialistic.

628
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:03,320
Don't you know?

629
00:33:03,520 --> 00:33:04,560
Know what?

630
00:33:05,560 --> 00:33:06,840
Dr. Xu's dad...

631
00:33:06,840 --> 00:33:08,199
is the director of Ruirong Hospital...

632
00:33:08,199 --> 00:33:10,199
and the secretary-general of the Medical Doctor Association.

633
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:12,199
He's also the one leading the survey team.

634
00:33:12,560 --> 00:33:14,040
The director of Ruirong Hospital?

635
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:16,320
That's one of the best hospitals in Shanghai.

636
00:33:17,480 --> 00:33:18,840
I didn't know Dr. Xu...

637
00:33:18,840 --> 00:33:20,719
came from such a sophisticated family.

638
00:33:21,600 --> 00:33:23,080
Stop being so emotional.

639
00:33:23,199 --> 00:33:24,639
Go and kiss his ass when you have time.

640
00:33:26,520 --> 00:33:27,520
No.

641
00:33:27,879 --> 00:33:29,560
I was just emotional for a moment.

642
00:33:31,919 --> 00:33:32,919
Then...

643
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:35,600
This person is Dr. Xu's dad.

644
00:33:35,919 --> 00:33:37,679
Why is Dr. Xu so upset?

645
00:33:38,159 --> 00:33:39,719
I heard from my friends in Ruirong...

646
00:33:40,159 --> 00:33:42,359
that the father and son don't get along.

647
00:33:42,520 --> 00:33:45,199
Director Xu always thinks of Dr. Xu as useless.

648
00:33:51,719 --> 00:33:53,119
This is not a good sign.

649
00:33:54,959 --> 00:33:56,639
He hasn't contacted you for so many years.

650
00:33:56,879 --> 00:33:57,879
Why is he suddenly coming here?

651
00:33:59,439 --> 00:34:01,560
He must be targeting you.

652
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:03,439
He still wants me to go to Ruirong.

653
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:05,959
That's good too.

654
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:08,600
Go back and continue to be the son of the boss.

655
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:10,719
It's much cooler than...

656
00:34:10,719 --> 00:34:12,040
being a doctor here.

657
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:13,800
Since it's so impressive,

658
00:34:14,919 --> 00:34:16,040
I'll recommend you.

659
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:18,000
My dad is quite interested in you.

660
00:34:18,159 --> 00:34:19,159
Forget it.

661
00:34:19,240 --> 00:34:20,520
I'm not interested in him.

662
00:34:24,119 --> 00:34:25,199
So what now?

663
00:34:26,399 --> 00:34:27,760
Have you come up with a plan?

664
00:34:27,959 --> 00:34:28,959
Yes.

665
00:34:29,159 --> 00:34:30,199
What is it?

666
00:34:30,319 --> 00:34:31,480
I'll cross the bridge...

667
00:34:32,119 --> 00:34:33,369
when I come to it.

668
00:34:36,480 --> 00:34:37,600
Si Si.

669
00:34:37,759 --> 00:34:39,369
Give me the lab results for the patient in bed nine.

670
00:34:39,369 --> 00:34:40,369
Okay.

671
00:34:41,409 --> 00:34:42,409
Thank you.

672
00:34:42,929 --> 00:34:43,929
Yi Ran.

673
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:50,560
Dad.

674
00:34:50,929 --> 00:34:53,409
When will you understand how I feel?

675
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:56,319
You'll have a position in Ruirong.

676
00:34:57,520 --> 00:34:59,600
Do you know...

677
00:34:59,639 --> 00:35:01,000
what that position in Ruirong means?

678
00:35:03,520 --> 00:35:05,560
It's something people can't get...

679
00:35:05,560 --> 00:35:07,000
no matter how hard they try.

680
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,119
But what are you doing?

681
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:10,520
Can you just throw it away like that?

682
00:35:11,929 --> 00:35:13,759
Have you thought about my feelings?

683
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:15,560
My reputation?

684
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:17,480
My situation?

685
00:35:18,759 --> 00:35:20,239
I know you're talented...

686
00:35:20,239 --> 00:35:21,369
and you work hard.

687
00:35:21,369 --> 00:35:22,839
But in this place,

688
00:35:22,839 --> 00:35:25,279
just talent and hard work is not enough.

689
00:35:28,279 --> 00:35:29,679
I've gone from being a clinical specialist...

690
00:35:30,560 --> 00:35:32,080
to a hospital administrator.

691
00:35:32,889 --> 00:35:34,639
I've been up and down.

692
00:35:35,239 --> 00:35:37,319
I never dared to slack off.

693
00:35:37,319 --> 00:35:38,319
Why?

694
00:35:38,440 --> 00:35:40,080
Did I do it for myself?

695
00:35:40,080 --> 00:35:41,679
It's for you!

696
00:35:43,159 --> 00:35:45,520
So that you could get a better starting point.

697
00:35:45,719 --> 00:35:47,000
For your future,

698
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:48,929
I paved the way for you.

699
00:35:49,040 --> 00:35:50,369
- Dad. - All right.

700
00:35:51,119 --> 00:35:52,560
I don't want to hear your excuses.

701
00:35:53,119 --> 00:35:54,639
Go to Jiang now...

702
00:35:54,719 --> 00:35:55,719
and quit your job.

703
00:35:55,719 --> 00:35:56,839
I'm not trying to make excuses.

704
00:35:57,679 --> 00:35:58,759
And I won't quit either.

705
00:35:58,759 --> 00:36:00,600
Do you hate Ruirong that much?

706
00:36:01,080 --> 00:36:02,369
Or do you hate me?

707
00:36:02,369 --> 00:36:04,799
I don't hate Ruirong or you.

708
00:36:05,279 --> 00:36:06,889
I'm an adult.

709
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:09,119
I don't want to live under your rules all the time.

710
00:36:09,279 --> 00:36:11,159
I want to do things my own way.

711
00:36:11,159 --> 00:36:12,839
You have no right to decide for yourself.

712
00:36:19,319 --> 00:36:20,369
Yi Ran.

713
00:36:21,409 --> 00:36:22,679
What can you learn...

714
00:36:22,719 --> 00:36:24,199
by staying here?

715
00:36:24,719 --> 00:36:26,409
If you like the emergency department,

716
00:36:26,440 --> 00:36:29,000
you should go to Ruirong's emergency department.

717
00:36:29,560 --> 00:36:31,369
Ruirong's emergency department...

718
00:36:31,369 --> 00:36:33,480
is one of the best in the nation.

719
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:34,799
Compared to Ruirong,

720
00:36:36,159 --> 00:36:37,319
I like here better.

721
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:40,040
The people I work with here are nice.

722
00:36:41,759 --> 00:36:43,889
I've learned a lot from them.

723
00:36:44,440 --> 00:36:46,929
I see more people and things here...

724
00:36:47,480 --> 00:36:49,839
and the gap between my reality, ideals, and goals...

725
00:36:49,929 --> 00:36:51,440
as a doctor

726
00:36:51,889 --> 00:36:54,440
I see myself growing and improving every day.

727
00:36:55,279 --> 00:36:57,239
My mindset is constantly maturing.

728
00:36:57,319 --> 00:36:58,409
Mature?

729
00:36:58,839 --> 00:37:00,520
I think it's childish.

730
00:37:01,199 --> 00:37:03,279
There is no room for discussion.

731
00:37:03,560 --> 00:37:06,279
Nor can you negotiate.

732
00:37:07,239 --> 00:37:08,440
You must do it.

733
00:37:08,799 --> 00:37:10,719
And you must do it my way.

734
00:37:10,839 --> 00:37:11,929
Dad, listen to me.

735
00:37:11,929 --> 00:37:13,560
Report to Ruirong at the end of this month.

736
00:37:27,639 --> 00:37:29,960
How did the talk with your bossy CEO go?

737
